<subSubSection id="8FAA1E8DFFB9FF8CFD4921A6FC6A8BDD" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFB9FF8AFD4921A6FCA88C10" blockId="42.[670,1199,889,1763]" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">
IDENTIFICATION: 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFB9FF8AFC8B21A6FBAB8AF0" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[889,1056,948,971]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 1978), Davis (1976b), and 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFB9FF8AFC9921C3FCBF8D3E" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
provided descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB9FF8AFCA6261EFBC48D18" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[852,1103,1036,1059]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFCA6261EFBC48D18" box="[852,1103,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">Noctilio albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Davis (1976b) recognized four subspecies in his revision: 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFD0D2655FC998D65" box="[767,786,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFCDE2655FCB08D65" box="[812,827,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB9FF8AFCA62655FC128D65" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[852,921,1095,1118]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Choeroniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFCA62655FC128D65" box="[852,921,1095,1118]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(southern Mexico to northwestern Venezuela), 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC202676FC6E8D40" box="[978,997,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC042676FB8E8D40" box="[1014,1029,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFBE72676FBD78D40" box="[1045,1116,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">affinis</emphasis>
(western Amazonia, northern Venezuela and the coastal Guianas), 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC8D268DFC198D8D" box="[895,914,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC58268DFC328D8D" box="[938,953,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB9FF8AFC22268DFBC78D8D" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[976,1100,1183,1206]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC22268DFBC78D8D" box="[976,1100,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(southeastern Venezuela and southern Guyana to eastern Brazil), and 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB9FF8AFC6B26CBFB258DCB" authorityName="Davis" authorityYear="1976" box="[921,1198,1241,1264]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="albiventris" subSpecies="cabrerai">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC6B26CBFC278DCB" box="[921,940,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC3326CBFB258DCB" box="[961,1198,1241,1264]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">albiventris cabrerai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(southwestern Brazil, Paraguay, and northern Argentina).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFB9FF8AFD492723FB258FD8" blockId="42.[670,1199,889,1763]" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">
According to Davis (1976b), the coastal Guianan form, 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFCAB275DFCE78C5D" box="[857,876,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC8D275DFC058C5D" box="[895,910,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC53275DFC638C5D" box="[929,1000,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">affinis</emphasis>
, is substantially larger than the nominate subspecies. Although some overlap in size was reported in length of the maxillary toothrow in both sexes and in forearm length of females (op. cit.), nonoverlapping measurements were given for forearm length in males (56.3â60.3 mm in 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFD32240EFD588F08" box="[704,723,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFD14240EFD7E8F08" box="[742,757,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB9FF8AFCFA240EFC0F8F08" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[776,900,1564,1587]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFCFA240EFC0F8F08" box="[776,900,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 61.5â70.0 mm in 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFB80240EFB0E8F08" box="[1138,1157,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFB6A240EFB2C8F08" box="[1176,1191,1564,1587]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFD6C242BFD6E8F6B" box="[670,741,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">affinis</emphasis>
). Unfortunately, the geographic samples closest to Paracou that Davis personally examined were from coastal Guyana (representing 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFCF22483FCCC8F93" box="[768,839,1681,1704]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">affinis</emphasis>
) and near the mouth of the Amazon (representing 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB9FF8AFC5F24BDFBA28FFD" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[941,1065,1711,1734]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB9FF8AFC5F24BDFBA28FFD" box="[941,1065,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), leaving a wide hiatus with no representative specimens
</paragraph>
<caption id="93CF1D8EFFB8FF8BFF682419FE3D8F4B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4545100" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4545100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4545100/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="43" startId="43.[154,192,1547,1568]" targetBox="[229,1130,208,1525]" targetPageId="43">
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFB8FF8BFF682419FE3D8F4B" blockId="43.[128,1233,1547,1648]" pageId="43" pageNumber="43">
Fig. 23. Roost of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB8FF8BFE982419FDB68F1B" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[362,573,1547,1568]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Saccopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leptura">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFB8FF8BFE982419FDB68F1B" box="[362,573,1547,1568]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="43">Saccopteryx leptura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in closedÂ­canopy secondary growth at Paracou. Four individuals were found roosting together about 2 m above the ground in the semicylindrical interior of this broken trunk (arrow). Other roosts of this species were found in equally wellÂ­lighted spaces between the buttresses of living trees.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFBFFF8CFFAC216BFE7E8D8E" blockId="44.[94,623,889,1763]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">
examined (i.e., Surinam, French Guiana, and the Brazilian State of AmapaÂ´). Based on the measurements of a Surinamese specimen reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFBFFF8CFF2621C3FE088AD3" author="Husson, A. M." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[212,387,977,1000]" journalOrPublisher="Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" refId="ref95767" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zool. Verh. Rijksmus. Nat. Hist. (Leiden) 52: 282 pp. 1 30 pls." title="The bats of Suriname" type="book" year="1962">Husson (1962)</bibRefCitation>
, however, Davis extended the presumed range of 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFE2521FDFD958D3D" box="[471,542,1007,1030]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">affinis</emphasis>
to include the entire coastal region of the Guianas. Based on Davisâ (1976b) map (reproduced by 
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFBFFF8CFF1E2654FDE58D66" author="Hood, C. S. &amp; J. Pitocchelli" bookContentInfo="5 pp." box="[236,622,1094,1117]" journalOrPublisher="Mamm. Species 197" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" refId="ref95645" refString="Hood, C. S., and J. Pitocchelli 1983. Noctilio albiventris. Mamm. Species 197: 5 pp." title="Noctilio albiventris" type="book" year="1983">Hood and Pitocchelli [1983]</bibRefCitation>
without the dots indicating collecting localities), specimens from French Guiana would presumably represent 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFE91268DFEFD8D8D" box="[355,374,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFE75268DFE1D8D8D" box="[391,406,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFE55268DFE658D8D" box="[423,494,1183,1206]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">affinis</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFBFFF8CFF8926AEFF228FD8" blockId="44.[94,623,889,1763]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">
Contrary to that expectation, our specimen from Paracou and another reported from nearby Sinnamary (
<bibRefCitation id="A32130F7FFBFFF8CFECD26E4FF7C8C10" author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" journalOrPublisher="Mammalia" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" pagination="509 - 559" part="54" refId="ref91807" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 559." title="The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach" type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and CharlesÂ­Dominique, 1990</bibRefCitation>
) are morphologically intermediate to 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFF312723FE818C73" box="[195,266,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">affinis</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFBFFF8CFEB92723FE4C8C73" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[331,455,1329,1352]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFEB92723FE4C8C73" box="[331,455,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as those taxa were described by Davis (1976b). Maxillary toothrow lengths of both French Guianan specimens fall in the zone of overlap between the low end of the range of variation reported for 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFF0127D6FE8D8CE0" box="[243,262,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFEE527D6FEAD8CE0" box="[279,294,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">a</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFEC427D6FEF68CE0" box="[310,381,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">affinis</emphasis>
and the high end of the range of variation reported for 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFDF527F3FD918CC3" box="[519,538,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFDDF27F3FDB78CC3" box="[557,572,1505,1528]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">a</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFBFFF8CFDBF27F3FF4F8F2D" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFDBF27F3FF4F8F2D" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The forearm measurement of the female reported by Brosset and CharlesÂ­ Dominique (1990) similarly falls in the zone of subspecific overlap, while the forearm measurement of our male (table 9) fits within the gap that Davis reported between the ranges of variation of 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFEA924BDFE298FFD" box="[347,418,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">affinis</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFBFFF8CFE0024BDFDE58FFD" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[498,622,1711,1734]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFE0024BDFDE58FFD" box="[498,622,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">albiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C70F4D06FFBFFF8CFD4922C4FC6A8BDD" blockId="44.[670,1199,214,862]" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">
Although Davis (1976b: fig. 5) mapped a discontinuity between the geographic distributions of 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFCED2300FCB98812" box="[799,818,274,297]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5C49114FFBFFF8CFCB62300FCD88812" box="[836,851,274,297]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="44">a</emphasis>
. 
